  "texts": [
    "However, in applications, N is likely to be large, and we may not have so many ancillae.",
    "Suppose we have only O(N) ancilla qubitsenough to prepare one state in O(log(N)) depth, but not w states.",
    "Naively, we could prepare the w states in series, incurring depth O(w log(N)).",
    "However, since the spacetime allocation required for a single state preparation is O(N), the spacetime allocation for preparing w states is O(wN), suggesting that if the O(N) ancillae are used reused optimally, we might achieve O(w) total depth, rather than O(w log(N)).",
    "Indeed, we now illustrate that using our SP+CSP protocol one can accomplish the task in depth O(w + log(N)), which is constant O(1) depth per copy when w ≥ Ω(log(N)).There are two essential properties in the single-copy arbitrary state preparation method we described in section 3:1."
